com.google.appinventor.components.scripts

Class ComponentProcessor.ComponentInfo

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.appinventor.components.scripts.ComponentProcessor.Feature
      • com.google.appinventor.components.scripts.ComponentProcessor.ComponentInfo
  • Enclosing class:
    ComponentProcessor

    protected final class ComponentProcessor.ComponentInfo
extends ComponentProcessor.Feature
    Represents an App Inventor component, including its designer properties, Simple properties, methods, and events.

    • Method Detail

      • getHelpDescription

        protected String getHelpDescription()
        A brief description of this component to be shown when the user requests help in the Designer. This is obtained from the first of the following that was provided in the source code for the component:
        1. DesignerComponent.designerHelpDescription()
        2. DesignerComponent.description()
        3. the Javadoc preceding the beginning of the class corresponding to the component

      • getCategory

        protected String getCategory()
        Returns the name of this component's category within the Designer, as displayed (for example, "Screen Arrangement").
        Returns:
        the name of this component's Designer category

      • getCategoryString

        protected String getCategoryString()
        Returns the String representation of the EnumConstant corresponding to this component's category within the Designer (for example, "ARRANGEMENTS"). Usually, you should use getCategory() instead.
        Returns:
        the EnumConstant representing this component's Designer category

      • getVersion

        protected int getVersion()
        Returns the version number of this component, as specified by DesignerComponent.version().
        Returns:
        the version number of this component

      • getShowOnPalette

        Returns:
        whether this component is shown on the Designer palette

      • getNonVisible

        protected boolean getNonVisible()
        Returns whether this component is non-visible on the device's screen, as specified by DesignerComponent.nonVisible(). Examples of non-visible components are LocationSensor and Clock.
        Returns:
        true if the component is non-visible, false otherwise

      • getIconName

        protected String getIconName()
